### Core Structural Refactoring

#### 1. Eliminating the Wildcard Host Leak (`norust.md` Refactor)

String-based wildcards (`"*"`) introduce structural parsing bugs and ambient authority leaks. The pure `.lln` runtime enforces explicit algebraic variants instead of loose text configuration strings.

```rust
;; Location: packages-logicn/logicn-core-security/src/capabilities.lln

type NetworkTarget =
  | ExplicitHost(String)  ;; Must evaluate to an exact FQDN or fixed IP
  | UnrestrictedInternet  ;; Requires separate explicit policy authorization

type NetworkConstraint = {
  target: NetworkTarget,
  allowed_port: U16,
  require_tls: Bool
}

flow evaluateNetworkEgress(req: NetworkConstraint, gran: NetworkConstraint) -> Bool {
  let hostVerified = match (req.target, gran.target) {
    (NetworkTarget.ExplicitHost(r_host), NetworkTarget.ExplicitHost(g_host)) => r_host == g_host,
    (_, NetworkTarget.UnrestrictedInternet) => true,
    _ => false
  };
  
  return hostVerified && (req.allowed_port == gran.allowed_port) && (req.require_tls == gran.require_tls);
}

```

#### 2. Re-engineering `scanForSecretLiteral` via Cleartext Slices

Comparing cryptographic SHA-256 hashes against a continuous cleartext data stream is mathematically broken for substring lookups. To enforce un-bypassable data scrubbers in pure `.lln` without leaking core credentials to guest registers, the DSS stores short, cleartext prefix tokens (minimum 8 characters) in a dedicated write-only lookup structure.

```rust
;; Location: packages-logicn/logicn-core-security/src/sink-monitor.lln

type SecretSinkCache = mut {
  tracked_prefixes: List<String>
}

global active_sink_monitor: SecretSinkCache = SecretSinkCache { tracked_prefixes: List.new() }

flow registerSecretTrackingPrefix(rawSecret: String) -> Void {
  if (String.length(rawSecret) >= 12) {
    ;; Extract an 8-character cleartext window for streaming match interception
    let signaturePrefix = String.substring(rawSecret, 0, 8);
    active_sink_monitor.tracked_prefixes.append(signaturePrefix);
  }
}

flow evaluateStreamingOutput(rawPayload: String) -> String {
  for prefix in active_sink_monitor.tracked_prefixes {
    if (crypto::contains_substring_match(rawPayload, prefix)) {
      ;; Halt execution across the entire virtual machine loop immediately
      runtime::triggerHardwareTrap(3001); ;; Trap Code: LLN-SECRET-BREACH
    }
  }
  return rawPayload;
}

```

